To handle multiple input criteria dynamically in your repository class and queries.properties, you should follow a structured approach:

1️⃣ Queries in queries.properties

Define query templates with placeholders ({}) for each dynamic condition. Example:

baseQuery=SELECT * FROM c WHERE 1=1
filterByAddressCode= AND c.addressCode = @addressCode
filterByCharacterSet= AND c.characterSetType = @characterSetType
filterByPostalCode= AND c.postalCode = @postalCode
filterByCountry= AND c.country = @country
filterByPrefecture= AND c.prefecture = @prefecture
filterByCity= AND c.city = @city
filterByTown= AND c.town = @town
filterByLane= AND c.lane = @lane
filterByEffectiveDate= AND c.effectiveDate = @effectiveDate
filterByTerminationDate= AND c.terminationDate = @terminationDate

2️⃣ Repository Class (AddressRepository.java)

This class will dynamically build queries based on available criteria.

import com.azure.cosmos.CosmosContainer;
import com.azure.cosmos.models.SqlQuerySpec;
import com.azure.cosmos.models.SqlParameter;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

@Repository
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class AddressRepository {

    private final CosmosContainer cosmosContainer;
    private final QueryPropertyFileConfig queryConfig;
    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(AddressRepository.class);

    public List<AddressModel> searchWithDynamicQuery(AddressSearchConditions searchConditions) {
        logger.info("[QUERY START] Searching address with conditions: {}", searchConditions);

        StringBuilder queryBuilder = new StringBuilder(queryConfig.getQuery("baseQuery"));
        List<SqlParameter> parameters = new ArrayList<>();

        if (searchConditions.getAddressCode() != null) {
            queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByAddressCode"));
            parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@addressCode", searchConditions.getAddressCode()));
        }

        if (searchConditions.getAddress() != null) {
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getCharacterSetType() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByCharacterSet"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@characterSetType", searchConditions.getAddress().getCharacterSetType()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getPostalCode() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByPostalCode"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@postalCode", searchConditions.getAddress().getPostalCode()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getCountry() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByCountry"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@country", searchConditions.getAddress().getCountry()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getPrefecture() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByPrefecture"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@prefecture", searchConditions.getAddress().getPrefecture()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getCity() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByCity"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@city", searchConditions.getAddress().getCity()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getTown() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByTown"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@town", searchConditions.getAddress().getTown()));
            }
            if (searchConditions.getAddress().getLane() != null) {
                queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByLane"));
                parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@lane", searchConditions.getAddress().getLane()));
            }
        }

        if (searchConditions.getEffectiveDate() != null) {
            queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByEffectiveDate"));
            parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@effectiveDate", searchConditions.getEffectiveDate().toString()));
        }

        if (searchConditions.getTerminationDate() != null) {
            queryBuilder.append(queryConfig.getQuery("filterByTerminationDate"));
            parameters.add(new SqlParameter("@terminationDate", searchConditions.getTerminationDate().toString()));
        }

        long queryStartTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
        SqlQuerySpec querySpec = new SqlQuerySpec(queryBuilder.toString(), parameters);

        List<AddressModel> results = cosmosContainer
                .queryItems(querySpec, new CosmosQueryRequestOptions(), AddressModel.class)
                .stream()
                .toList();

        logger.info("[QUERY END] Query executed. Results found: {}, Processing time: {} ms",
                results.size(), System.currentTimeMillis() - queryStartTime);
        logger.debug("Raw database response: {}", results);

        return results;
    }
}

3️⃣ Query Property Configuration Class (QueryPropertyFileConfig.java)

This will load the query properties.

import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;
import java.util.Properties;

@Configuration
public class QueryPropertyFileConfig {

    @Value("${query.file.path}")
    private String queriesResourcePath;

    private final Properties queries = new Properties();

    @PostConstruct
    public void loadQueries() throws Exception {
        try (InputStreamReader reader = new InputStreamReader(
                getClass().getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(queriesResourcePath),
                StandardCharsets.UTF_8)) {
            queries.load(reader);
        }
    }

    public String getQuery(String key) {
        return queries.getProperty(key, "");
    }
}

✅ Key Takeaways
	1.	Dynamic Queries → We only append conditions if values are present, avoiding unnecessary filters.
	2.	Properties-Based Queries → The query structure is easily maintainable via queries.properties.
	3.	Logging for Debugging → Info logs provide query execution details, and debug logs capture raw responses.
	4.	Lombok for Simplicity → @RequiredArgsConstructor auto-generates a constructor for dependencies.

